or just a sentence, or even a fleeting phrase, into the final text.
As the president's chief speechwriter, Edmonds is the guardian of
the computer disc containing the speech's latest draft, and the
coordinator of the policy proposals, accolades, reflections and
humorous asides that will pop up Thursday night on Clinton's
teleprompter. By Marc Lacey.
