<HEADLINE>
WE STILL DON'T MISS NFL
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ You knew it'd all come around to another
L.A.-vs.-Houston battle, and the best thing that can happen in
SBXXXIV is a Rambo take-no-prisoners victory.
</P>
<P>
   That way, we can look them former 20-gallon-hat Oilers fans in
the blackeye and honestly spit out with our chew: ``Y'all know,
even with a Super Bowl title, we still don't care that our team
left town and 'specially that no one came to our rescue to fill
that huuuuuge void.''
</P>
<P>
   'Cause if Fisher's Titanics somehow ram through the Vermeilians
of St. Lou on Sunday, dem bums in Texas will be claiming some sort
of relative credit ...
</P>
<P>
   __Already the hot prediction is this'll be the lowest-rated
S'Bowl of all time. Which is the kinda numbers game crud that Al
Michaels is just tired of hearing.
</P>
<P>
   ``There's so much hocus-pocus'' with Neilsen ratings, said the
ABC play-by-play man, who'll be doing his fourth Supergame (but
first without Frank Gifford and Dan Dierdorf.
</P>
<P>
   ``A few people in the sales department care about (ratings), but
outside of that, what does it mean anyway? Each weekend, they print
which movie was the biggest at the box office. Does the general
public care? Unless they're a shareholder?'' ...
</P>
<P>
   __There'll be about 125 million people watching, so what else do
ya need to know? ...
</P>
<P>
   __Tickets to the big shin-dig $350 face value, about $1,000-plus
through scalpers ...
</P>
<P>
   __Former UCLA point guard Michael Warren isn't losing his hair
over the Bruins' roller-coaster season. He's actually been
folically challenged since his playing days more than 25 years ago.
</P>
<P>
   He admits in a recent edition of The Star that he wore a
hairpiece back when he co-starred on ``Hill Street Blues.''
Warren's acting career has been revived with a recurring role on
the new Steven Bochco CBS drama ``City of Angels.'' ...
</P>
<P>
   __Isn't Henry Bibby's success at USC the ultimate dig at UCLA's
program? Either that or the fact Bill Walton steered his kid to
Lute Olson ...
</P>
<P>
   __To those delusional ``Michael Jordan for President''
campaigners _ see, he's prez . .. and in Washington. ...
</P>
<P>
   __Tyra Banks will not only sing on Kobe Bryant's upcoming rap
album but perform his first single ``K-O-B-E'' during the Feb. 12
NBA Teamup Celebration on TV. ...
</P>
<P>
   __The latest Men's Fitness magazine has Jason ``Best Abs in the
NFL'' Sehorn showing off on its cover. It's easy to keep those abs
bruise-free when you're not on the field of play. ...
</P>
<P>
   __No one has clearly explained yet how John Rocker's comments
could appear in a magazine owned by Time Warner, co-owned by Ted
Turner, who owns the Atlanta Braves, who pay Rocker's salary....
</P>
<P>
   __Playboy reports at a recent auction of baseball memorabilia, a
Marilyn Monroe-cover magazine signed by Joe DiMaggio fetched
$40,250, much more than what was spent on Ty Cobb's dentures
($7,475). ...
</P>
<P>
   __The L.A. Sports Council, lobbying on behalf of Staples Center,
wanted the 2001 NHL All-Star Game, which last week was handed to
Denver. ...
</P>
<P>
   __The Arena Football League's upcoming season is in jeopardy
because of a labor dispute. Some will say it's just another sign
that somehow pro football in L.A. isn't meant to be. We'll look at
the big picture: The AFL isn't meant to be.
</P>
