<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Friendly skies get annoying with oversized carry-ons
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ You are on a plane, carrying a small bag.
Overhead compartment after overhead compartment is filled with one
humongous carry-on bag after another. After a fruitless search, you
cram your bag under the seat and have a miserable, cramped flight.
Technology has come to the luggage market and has made the carry-on
bag the most annoying thing flying the friendly skies. In recent
years, carry-on bags have become more than carriers of magazines
and toothbrushes; they are now lumbering, canvas Winnebagos on
wheels, craftily designed to fit into the overhead bin exactly. Not
only that, they crowd aisles, slow down boarding and deplaning and
they make a heckuva bump on the noggin when they shift during
flight. While we know we can't outlaw them, we can at least make
them the annoying gadget of the week.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
