</P>
<P>
   $14.95.) A physiologist attributes Western dominance to
</P>
<P>
   geographical advantages. (b)
</P>
<P>
   8. (x) THE PROFESSOR AND THE MADMAN, by Simon Winchester.
</P>
<P>
   (HarperPerennial, $13.) How a murderer helped James
</P>
<P>
   Murray compile the Oxford English Dictionary.
</P>
<P>
   9. (x) THE SEAT OF THE SOUL, by Gary Zukav. (Fireside/S&AMP;S,
</P>
<P>
   $12.) How daily activities can be enhanced by feelings
</P>
<P>
   of meaning and purpose. (b)
</P>
<P>
   10. (x) THE MILLIONAIRE NEXT DOOR, by Thomas J. Stanley
</P>
<P>
   and William D. Danko. (Pocket, $14.) An analysis
</P>
<P>
   of the lives of wealthy Americans. (b)
</P>
<P>
   11. A WALK IN THE WOODS, by Bill Bryson. (Broadway, $13.)
</P>
<P>
   A journalist finds beauty and humor while hiking the
</P>
<P>
   Appalachian Trail.
</P>
<P>
   12. THE GIFTS OF THE JEWS, by Thomas Cahill.
