<P>
   &UR; OTHER PRO FOOTBALL &LR;
</P>
<P>
   FBN-ARATON-COLUMN (Hempstead, N.Y.) _ Sports of The Times column
on the appointment of Al Groh as the new Jets coach, with Bill
Parcells remaining on the scene in what Groh can only hope will be
a supportive role. By Harvey Araton.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-JETS-GROH (Hempstead, N.Y.) _ After several weeks without a
coach or an owner, the Jets now have both, with Robert Wood Johnson
on hand at the Jets complex Monday to introduce Al Groh, formerly
the team's linebackers coach, as the new head coach. Also on hand
is Bill Parcells, who will spell out just what his role with the
team will now be. By Gerald Eskenazi.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-CHIEFS-THOMAS (Kansas City) _ Derrick Thomas, one of the
NFL's most dominant defensive players, was hospitalized with
serious injuries from a car wreck that killed a close friend.
(Summary from wires)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; OTHER SPORTS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BKN-KNICKS-SONICS (New York) _ Seattle at the Knicks, 7:30 p.m.
EST start. By Mike Wise.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-NETS-BLAZERS (Portland, Ore.) _ N.J. Nets at Portland, 10
p.m. EST start. By Chris Broussard.
</P>
<P>
   AMERICAS-CUP (Auckland, New Zealand) _ The final round of the
challenger series _ a best five-of-nine affair _ begins with
Italy's Prada and America One going at it on the water.
</P>
<P>
   For information and repeats call the News Service at (888)
346-9867 or (212) 556-1927. And be sure to look for other sports
stories from our partners: The Boston Globe, Cox News Service,
Hearst News Service, The Arizona Republic, Kansas City Star, Fort
Worth Star-Telegram, Los Angeles Daily News, San Francisco
Chronicle and Seattle Post-Intelligencer.
</P>
