businessmen.
</P>
<P>
   ``Texans know that Governor Bush has received broad-based
support from people of all walks of life across the state for his
agenda of improving public schools and cutting taxes,'' said a Bush
spokesman.
</P>
<P>
   Many of the large donors also feature in the list of Bush's
Pioneers, each of whom promised to raise $100,000.
</P>
<P>
   In federal campaigns there is an individual limit of $1,000 on
contributions to candidates. But more can be given to Political
Action Committees, and in some companies, many individuals combine
to give money to candidates.
</P>
<P>
   ``What George W. Bush and his money men are really `pioneering,'
is the next generation of the political arms race, where the sky's
