finance case with important national implications, the Supreme
Court on Monday decisively upheld limits on campaign contributions
and rejected the argument that inflation has rendered
unconstitutionally low the $1,000 limit it upheld 24 years ago. The
6-3 decision left states with considerable latitude either to adopt
the federal limit, still the $1,000 the court upheld in its
much-disputed Buckley vs. Valeo decision, or to experiment with
even lower contribution caps, as a number of states recently have.
