 (Eds.: Newspapers that used the Boston Globe story MEDIA-COLUMN (e)
by Mark Jurkowitz, which moved Jan. 20, will wish to use the
following corrective.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Because of incorrect information given the reporter, a Boston
Globe column included the wrong circulation data for The (Colorado
Springs) Gazette. Rather than seeing a circulation increase in
December 1999, compared with the same month in 1998, circulation
for December 1999 was actually down 10,446 copies.
</P>
