<HEADER>
A5040 &Cx1f; tad-z
u s BC-FBN-SBOWL-TUE-RAIL-CO     01-24 0519
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-SBOWL-TUE-RAIL-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    FAST FACTS
 &HT;    By Mark Schlabach
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AFC
</P>
<P>
   _ Titans running back Eddie George became the first player in
franchise history to rush for 100 yards or more in consecutive
postseason games.
</P>
<P>
   _ In a 19-16 victory at Indianapolis in the divisional playoffs,
George rushed for a franchise postseason record 162 yards on 26
carries, including a 68-yard run, also a postseason record for the
Titans.
</P>
<P>
   _ George gained 106 yards on 29 carries in a 22-16 victory
against Buffalo in the wild-card round.
</P>
<P>
   _ George rushed for a career-best 1,304 yards this season and
gained a career-high 1,762 yards from scrimmage with 13 touchdowns.
</P>
<P>
   _ With 5,365 yards, George became only the fourth player in NFL
history to rush for at least 1,200 yards in each of his first four
seasons. He joined Eric Dickerson (6,968), Earl Campbell (6,457)
and Barry Sanders (5,674).
</P>
<P>
   _ The Titans are 20-5 _ 7-0 this season _ when George rushes for
100 or more yards in a game.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Titans are 17-5 _ 5-1 this season _ when George runs for
at least one touchdown.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Titans are 15-0 _ 7-0 this season _ when George has at
least 27 carries.
</P>
<P>
   _ Titans fullback Lorenzo Neal, signed as a free agent from
Tampa Bay, scored a career-high three touchdowns this season.
</P>
<P>
   _ Titans quarterback Steve McNair rushed for eight touchdowns in
each of the past two seasons. Only New England's Steve Grogan (12
in 1976), Pittsburgh's Kordell Stewart (11 in 1997) and Detroit's
Greg Landry (nine in 1972) rushed for more.
</P>
<P>
   NFC
</P>
<P>
   _ The Rams gave up an average of 74.3 rushing yards per game..
</P>
<P>
   _ They did not allow a 100-yard rusher this season. The most
rushing yardage gained against the Rams was 77 yards by San
Francisco's Charlie Garner on Nov. 21.
</P>
<P>
   _ The longest run for a touchdown the Rams gave up in the
regular season was 10 yards by Titans quarterback Steve McNair.
</P>
<P>
   _ The longest run from scrimmage the Rams allowed was 40 yards
by Cleveland Browns quarterback Tim Couch.
</P>
<P>
   _ They gave up just four rushing touchdowns in 16 regular-season
games.
</P>
<P>
   _ New Orleans Saints back Lamar Smith and the Philadelphia
Eagles' Duce Staley had the most carries against the Rams, 18.
</P>
<P>
   _ Garner had the highest yards-per-carry average against the
Rams, 4.8.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Rams allowed runs of 21 yards or more just four times.
</P>
<P>
   _ Of the 318 rushes against the Rams in the regular season, 224
were 4 yards or less.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Carolina Panthers had the most rushing yards against the
Rams, 117.
</P>
<P>
   _ In the last four games of the regular season, the Rams did not
allow a team to rush for more than 69 yards._ Twice, the Rams
allowed just one rushing first down for a game _ against Detroit
and Phildelphia. The Lions had 14 passing first downs, the Eagles
nine.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Rams did not allow a regular-season rushing touchdown in
their last six games and eight of their last nine.
</P>
<P>
   Mark Schlabach writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution,
Atlanta, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
