<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Jan. 25 and thereafter. For questions about stories, contact the
Daily News, (818) 713-3705.
</P>
<P>
   API-SCHOOLS (Los Angeles) -- Many Los Angeles Unified schools
score near the bottom of a new statewide ranking of public school
performance. But the new Academic Performance Index, scheduled to
be released Tuesday, also shows that many of those same poorly
performing schools actually do better than other California
campuses with a similar mix of students. By David Baker. (Will move
on the ``n'' California news wire.)
</P>
<P>
   SPY-RUSSIAN (Los Angeles) -- A former Russian spy testified to a
congressional panel Monday in Los Angeles that he scouted U.S.
locations as potential drop sites for caches of weapons and money
for Soviet agents. But, Stanislav Lunev said he does not know if
supplies were placed in any of the locations. Members of Congress
want the White House to ask Russia for a list of the sites and
their contents. By Steve Carney. (Will move on the ``n'' California
and ``a'' national news wires.)
</P>
<P>
   SPEAKER-HERTZBERG (Sacramento) -- In a voice vote, the state
Assembly voted unanimously to make Bob Hertzberg, D-Van Nuys, the
next Speaker of the legislative chamber. The unanimous bipartisan
support was the first in memory for a first-time incoming speaker,
officials say. By Terri Hardy. (Will move on the ``n'' California
news wire.)
</P>
<P>
   AMGEN-EARNINGS (Los Angeles) -- The big question on analysts'
minds is whether Thousand Oaks-based Amgen will announce today it
has filed for FDA approval for two products it has been developing.
The company also is expected to beat Wall Street estimates when it
releases its quarterly earnings after the markets close. By Jason
Z. Cohen. (Will move on the ``f'' financial news wire.)
</P>
<P>
   LLOYD-COLUMN (Los Angeles) -- Ken Lloyd _ a specialist in
organizational behavior _ is a columnist for the Los Angeles Daily
News. His column moves Mondays in the ``f'' financial news file.
</P>
