the company's chief executive, Heidrick &AMP; Struggles International.
By Patrick McGeehan.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET.)
</P>
<P>
   (Bottom)
</P>
<P>
   MARKET (New York) _ Stock prices fell sharply in very heavy
trading Monday as investors shed positions in a wide array of
sectors, but especially technology, in advance of meetings next
week that are expected to produce an increase in short-term
interest rates. By Kenneth N. Gilpin.
</P>
