<HEADER>
A5203 &Cx1f; tad-z
u s BC-FBN-SBOWL-RUNDEFENSE-     01-24 0261
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-SBOWL-RUNDEFENSE-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    NFC run defense facts for Monday
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   _ The Rams gave up an average of 74.3 rushing yards per game.
</P>
<P>
   _ They did not allow a 100-yard rusher this season. The most
rushing yardage gained against the Rams was 77 yards by San
Francisco's Charlie Garner on Nov. 21.
</P>
<P>
   _ The longest run for a touchdown the Rams gave up in the
regular season was 10 yards by Titans quarterback Steve McNair.
</P>
<P>
   _ The longest run from scrimmage the Rams allowed was 40 yards
by Cleveland Browns quarterback Tim Couch.
</P>
<P>
   _ They gave up just four rushing touchdowns in 16 regular-season
games.
</P>
<P>
   _ New Orleans Saints back Lamar Smith and the Philadelphia
Eagles' Duce Staley had the most carries against the Rams, 18.
</P>
<P>
   _ Garner had the highest yards-per-carry average against the
Rams, 4.8.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Rams allowed runs of 21 yards or more just four times.
</P>
<P>
   _ Of the 318 rushes against the Rams in the regular season, 224
were 4 yards or less.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Carolina Panthers had the most rushing yards against the
Rams, 117.
</P>
<P>
   _ In the last four games of the regular season, the Rams did not
allow a team to rush for more than 69 yards.
</P>
<P>
   _ Twice, the Rams allowed just one rushing first down for a game
_ against Detroit and Phildelphia. The Lions had 14 passing first
downs, the Eagles nine.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Rams did not allow a regular-season rushing touchdown in
their last six games and eight of their last nine.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
