   Monday, Jan. 24, 2000:
</P>
<P>
   IOWA CAUCUSES:
</P>
<P>
   After a final flurry of campaigning, Republican and Democratic
presidential candidates shifted their attention to delivering
backers to Monday night's leadoff nominating caucuses.
</P>
<P>
   Additional photos of the candidates, as well as features on the
caucuses, will move by 10:00 p.m., EST.
</P>
<P>
   The following photos on the Iowa caucuses have moved as part of
today's New York Times Photo package:
</P>
<P>
   (NYT2) MOULTONBOROUGH, N.H. -- Jan. 24, 2000 -- MCCAIN --
Students listen to Sen. John McCain at the Moultonborough Academy
on Monday. McCain had New Hampshire to himself for the last time as
his rivals crisscrossed Iowa in the final hours before the caucuses
there. McCain did not contest Iowa.
</P>
<P>
   Photo by Monica Almeida
</P>
<P>
   (NYT3) SIOUX CITY, Iowa -- Jan. 24, 2000 -- IOWA-CAUCUSES-BUSH
-- Gov. George W. Bush talks with Rev. Dick Hardy at a resturant
during a campaign stop on Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Photo by Stephen Crowley.
</P>
<P>
   (NYT8) AMES, Iowa -- Jan. 24, 2000 -- IOWA-CAUCUSES-BRADLEY --
Bill Bradley, running for the Democratic presidential nomination,
during a campaign stop at Iowa State University on Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Photo by Keith Meyers.
</P>
<P>
   (NYT12) MOLINE, Ill. -- Jan. 24, 2000 -- IOWA-CAUCUSES-GORE --
Vice President Al Gore waves before boarding Air Force Two bound
for Des Moines.
</P>
<P>
   Photo by Paul Hosefros.
</P>
<P>
   (NYT23) DES MOINES, Iowa -- Jan. 24, 2000 --
IOWA-CAUCUSES-GORE-2 -- Gore works the phones at his Iowa campaign
headquarters.
</P>
