   (NYT4) URUS-MARTAN, Russia -- Jan. 24, 2000 -- RUSSIA-CHECHNYA
-- A woman and her grandchildren head towards a well for water in
the town in central Chechnya, Monday. Russian troops entered the
breakaway republic of Chechnya in September after Chechen-based
militants stormed villages in the neighboring Russian region of
Dagestan. The rebels also were blamed for a series of deadly
bombings of apartment houses in Moscow and two other cities in
September. (James Hill/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT3) SIOUX CITY, Iowa -- Jan. 24, 2000 -- IOWA-CAUCUSES-BUSH
