during a campaign stop on Monday. After a final flurry, Republican
and Democratic presidential candidates shifted attention to
delivering backers to Monday night's leadoff nominating caucuses,
and the front-runners publicly fretting that many of their
supporters might not bother turning out. (Stephen Crowley/The New
York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT2) MOULTONBOROUGH, N.H. -- Jan. 24, 2000 -- MCCAIN --
Students listen to Sen. John McCain at the Moultonborough Academy
on Monday. In a clear line of attack against George W. Bush,
McCain, running for the Republican presidential nomination, began
campaigning with the theme that he is ready to become president.
(Monica Almeida/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) LONG BRANCH, N.J. -- Jan. 24, 2000 -- NJ-SETONHALL-FIRE
-- Relatives and friends embrace outside St. Jerome Church on
Monday where funeral services for Frank S. Caltabilota took place.
More than 800 teary-eyed mourners turned out to say goodbye to
Caltabilota, one of three students who died in the dormitory fire
last week at Seton Hall University. (Dith Pran/The New York Times)
</P>
